org.chronos.chronodb.internal.api

Interface GetResult<T>

  • Type Parameters:
    T - The return type of the getValue() method.
    All Known Implementing Classes:
    GetResultImpl

    public interface GetResult<T>
    A GetResult is returned by a TemporalDataMatrix.get(long, String).

    It represents the result of a TemporalDataMatrix.get(long, String) call and includes the actual value as well as the associated validity period.

    Please note that the time range will always include the timestamp which was requested. Requesting different timestamps may produce different ranges on the same key. It is guaranteed that these ranges do not overlap for the same key.

      • isHit

        boolean isHit()
        Decides if this get result represents a "hit", i.e. the search ended up in a concrete entry.

        This method returns false in case that no entry matched the query. It returns true if an entry matched the query, even if that entry represents a deletion.

        If this method returns true, then getValue() will always return null (no match found). Otherwise, getValue() may return null to indicate an explicit deletion, or a non- null value to indicate an insert/update.

        Returns:
        true if the search produced a concrete result, or false if no key matched the query.
